<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taliban Capture Town in Northern Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Afghanistan's ruling Taliban
militia Thursday captured Ishkamish, a key town in the northern
province of Takhar, the Afghan Islamic Press (AIP) reported.
</P>
<P>
Taliban forces have been attacking opposition positions in the
Ishkamish district since they seized Nehreen and Borka towns in
neighboring Baghlan Province last week from forces loyal to chief
opposition commander Ahmed Masood.
</P>
<P>
Ishkamish's fall to Taliban control threatens Masood's supply
line from Takhar and Badakhsan provinces to his stronghold in the
Panjsher valley, according to the Pakistan-based AIP.
</P>
<P>
Details of the battle were not immediately available. 
</P>
</TEXT>
