<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Opposition Alliance Calls Off Hartal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The BNP (Bangladesh Nationalist
Party)-led four-party opposition alliance has decided at a meeting
to call off its scheduled countrywide hartal (destructive strike)
on August 6 in view of the extent of the deadly disease dengue
fever.
</P>
<P>
The opposition, however, will stage a countrywide demonstration
on that day to protest government failure and ineptness and demand
the resignation of the government.
</P>
<P>
In the capital Dhaka, the four parties will stage a joint
demonstration in observance of the program, BNP Vice-Chairman
Shamsul Islam told reporters Thursday.
</P>
<P>
the vice-chairman said the opposition withdrew its scheduled
hartal program due to the outbreak of dengue fever in an "epidemic
form"across the country which has claimed 16 lives according to
official account.
</P>
<P>
The opposition's decision to call off the hartal was made after
consultations with physicians and the people in general, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
