<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Approves New Electoral System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's cabinet of ministers
Thursday approved the introduction of a new electoral system to
replace the present proportionate representative system.
</P>
<P>
"The cabinet also decided to present this new electoral reform
proposal as the 17th amendment to the present constitution and to
refer the bill to the Supreme Court for its jurisdiction," said
Ariya Rubasinghe, director of information.
</P>
<P>
However, he did not elaborate on the new electoral system.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet decision comes at a time when the current
parliament is going to be dissolved on August 24 at the end of its
six-year term. The next parliamentary election must be held by the
first week of November. 
</P>
</TEXT>
