<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spain, Japan and South Korea to Host World Events </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Spain will host next year's Club
World Championships, while South Korea and Japan will co-host the
Confederations Cup, FIFA general secretary Michel Zen-Ruffinen
announced in Zurich on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Zen-Ruffinen said the world club event would take place in the
summer of 2001, featuring 12 teams, though the exact dates have
not been determined.
</P>
<P>
FIFA wants South Korea and Japan to host the 2001
Confederations Cup in order to make sure they have prepared well
for the 2002 World Cup, said Zen-Ruffinen.
</P>
<P>
The event, which will probably be in June, will feature the two
host nations along with Mexico as defending champion. The other
teams, representing the continental federations, will be France,
Brazil, Cameroon, Canada and Australia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
