<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Needs Over 1.3 Million Tons of Relief Food </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia on Friday appealed
to donors to increase relief food aid from 900.000 to more than 1.
3 million tons as the drought victims in the country had grown
from eight million to 10.3 million.
</P>
<P>
The officials of the Disaster Prevention and Preparedness
Commission (DPPC) said that 784,000 tons of food aid have been
pledged and 494,000 tons have been delivered so far.
</P>
<P>
The delivered amount of relief food included the 100,000 tons
purchased by the Ethiopian government from local markets, the
officials said.
</P>
<P>
Currently, four ships are unloading 115,000 tons of relief food
at the Port of Djibouti, while a ship was discharging 15,000 tons
of relief food at the Berbera Port of Somalia, they said.
</P>
<P>
According to the DPPC officials, an average of 5,000 tons of
relief food were being transported from central warehouses to
drought-affected areas per day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
