<HEADLINE> NATO to Hold Electronic War Game in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS,August 4(Xinhua)-- The North Atlantic Treaty
Organization(NATO)will hold an electronic war game from August 7
to 24 in the region of Landes,southwest France,said the French
Defense Ministry Friday.
</P>
<P>
More than 500 men from 14 NATO countries will participate in
the war game,which is held every two years.
</P>
<P>
The objective of the war game is to improve the existing
techniques and increasing the knowledge of the allied countries in
the field of defense and counter-attack against ground-to-air
missile attacks.
</P>
<P>
The war game will be carried out on the site of the center of
tests in Landes belonging to the French armament general direction,
and an air base in the Mont-de-Marsan area belonging to the French
air force. 
</P>
</TEXT>
