<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peru to Have Re-export Center in Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The official said that a business mission recently made a
visit to Panama and to other Central American countries to explore
the possibility of creating a center for the physical distribution
of Peruvian commodities being exported to that region.
</P>
<P>
Peruvian exports to the Central American countries amount now
to 50 million dollars a year, expecting to grow 20 percent with
the creation of a center of distribution in Panama.
</P>
<P>
Castillo said that one of the direct benefits for exporters
would be the reduction of export costs, because with this
warehouse the orders would be directly supplied.
</P>
<P>
Another advantage is that Central America will become a center
for the transfer of goods toward Mexico, which has an ample market
that will start working on January 1 of 2001.
</P>
<P>
Castillo said that the Central American market is very
attractive for small metal-mechanic, steel and iron, and building
material manufacturing enterprises.  
</P>
</TEXT>
