<DOCNO> XIE20000804.0038 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan Names Head of U.N. Office in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 4 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan Friday appointed Mussagy Jeichande as head of the
United Nations Office in Angola (UNOA).
</P>
<P>
The appointment came in a letter from Annan to the president
of the U.N. Security Council, which is being circulated here
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Jeichande, who is from Mozambique, was also appointed as
representative of Annan in Angola.
</P>
<P>
In a resolution adopted on October 15, 1999, the Security
Council authorized the establishment of UNOA for an initial period
of six months until April 15. On April 13,  a Security Council
resolution extended the mandate of UNOA until October 15.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Office will be staffed with personnel necessary to
maintain liaison with the political, military, police and other
civilian authorities, with the view to exploring measures for
restoring peace, assisting the Angolan people in capacity-building,
humanitarian assistance, the promotion of human rights, and
coordinating other activities.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations set up UNOA after the failure of its decade-
long peacekeeping operations in the southern African country and
the withdrawal of the peacekeepers at the request of the Angolan
Government.
</P>
<P>
Angola was plunged into a 36-year civil war between the
Angolan Government and the rebel National Union for the Total
Independence of Angola (UNITA), which is engaging in sales of
illicit diamonds to finance its war capabilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
