<HEADLINE> Suicides by French Prisoners on Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The number of suicides committed by
French prisoners has increased since the beginning of this year
compared to the same period last year, the French Prison
Administration said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Eight-five people have committed suicide in prison since the
beginning of this year, compared to 74 in the same period last
year, and 76 in 1998.
</P>
<P>
According to a study by the Ministry of Justice, more suicides
were committed in prison in the months of January, May, July and
August than other months.
</P>
<P>
Prisons in southeast France reported more suicides than those
in other parts of the country. Nine prisoners committed suicide in
January alone in prisons in southeast France. 
</P>
