<HEADLINE> Tung Updates Himself on Residents' Daily Life </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Chief Executive Tung Chee
Hwa Friday afternoon visited two families and a youth center in
Hung Hom to update himself on the daily life of the local
residents.
</P>
<P>
Tung said that the economy is recovering very strongly but not
all members of the community are benefiting from this recovery
because it does take time for this effect to filter down.
</P>
<P>
"But the fact is that all the figures show the economy is
growing strong and it will be sustainable and therefore we are
very confident that the benefit will eventually filter down and it
will not take too long," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Tung said that the purpose of the visit is really to try to get
a better understanding of the livelihood of the low income group
of citizens of Hong Kong. "I hope this will help me and my
colleagues in formulating our policies for the future," he said.
</P>
<P>
when he found out that the two families that he visited, both
focused very much on the education for the next generation, he
said, "To me, like all the other families in Hong Kong, we are all
very interested in better education for our younger generation,
because at the end of the day it is education which is going to
help people to get out of poverty to improve the quality of life."
.
</P>
<P>
The chief executive had also seen single parents and talked
with them. "I was deeply touched by the fact that they all take
time-out to do voluntary work," he said.
</P>
<P>
It is a tremendous spirit that makes Hong Kong work, he added,
hoping that the whole of Hong Kong will continue to move forward
in that kind of spirit of giving. 
</P>
