</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000804.0050 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepali Currency Weakens Against U.S. Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 4 Xinhua -- Nepal's currency rupee weakened
by 0.25 rupees Thursday following the depreciation of Indian
currency, according to a notice issued here Friday by Nepal's
central bank.
</P>
<P>
Nepal Rastra Bank, the country's central bank, refixed the
buying and selling rates of the dollar at 70.90 and 71.60 rupees
respectively from Wednesday's 70.65 and 71.35 rupees, said the
notice.
</P>
<P>
This is the third time within two months that the Nepali rupee
are devaluated against dollar in the wake of Indian currency's
depreciation.
</P>
<P>
The Nepali rupee is pegged to the Indian rupee at a fixed rate
of 1.6:1.
</P>
<P>
Nepali economists fear that consecutive depreciation of the
Nepali rupee will have tremendous pressure on the overall Nepali
economy.
</P>
<P>
"The devaluation will inflate price, which in turn poses
negative impact on foreign trade and economic growth," said Shiva
Sharma, an economist with Nepali Agricultural Development Bank.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
