<HEADLINE> 20 Killed in North India Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Over 600,000 people were affected by the floods, which hit 554
villages in 54 blocks across Bihar's 14 districts, the PTI quoted
state relief and rehabilitation department sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The overall flood situation was further deteriorating, with all
major rivers in the state having crossed danger marks at various
places along their courses, the PTI added.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this week, flash floods killed at least 105 people in
Himachal Pradesh state also in north India. There were also
reports of severe floods from northeast India's Assam state.
