<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top Leaders of S. Korea, DPRK Invited to Sydney Olympic Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The leaders of South Korea and the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) have been invited to
the Sydney Olympic Games, the South Korean Olympic Committee
announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
The committee said International Olympic Committee (IOC)
President Juan Antonio Samaranch has sent invitations to Olympic
committees of the two countries, asking top leaders of the nations,
Kim Dae-jung and Kim Jong Il, to attend the international sports
event simultaneously.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time the IOC has invited the leaders of the two
states to the Olympic Games. In its executive committee session,
the IOC decided the countries' national teams should enter the
opening ceremony simultaneously.
</P>
<P>
The games are scheduled to open on September 15 this year.
South Korea will send some 390 athletes while the DPRK will
reportedly dispatch a 50-member delegation to the games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
