<HEADLINE> France, Bulgaria to Hold Joint Military Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 4 (Xinhua) -- France and Bulgaria will hold joint
military exercises in the Balkan nation this autumn, the second of
its kind since last year, reported Agence France-Presse (AFP) on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
From October 10 to December 15, a unit of 700 soldiers from the
Second Armored Brigade based in Orleans, central France, will hold
with Bulgarian troops shooting range exercises at Novo Selo in
eastern Bulgaria, AFP quoted Bulgarian Defense Minister Velizar
Shalamanov and French ambassador in Sofia Dominique Chassard as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Some 50 heavy armored vehicles and 200 other vehicles of the
French armored brigade will join the exercises, said AFP.
</P>
<P>
Another French army unit held a joint exercise with Bulgarian
troops in autumn last year.
</P>
<P>
France is the first NATO country which has conducted joint
military exercises with Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
An Italian army unit will also hold joint military exercises
with Bulgarian troops this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
