<HEADLINE> HK Stocks Finish Higher on Wall Street Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong share prices finished
higher on Friday, propped by overnight Wall Street gains.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Hang Seng index climbed up 202.77 in the morning
session, but the gains were trimmed afterwards as investors,
unsure about the interest rate outlook, pocketed the profits,
analysts said.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng index closed 151.42, or 0.88 percent higher, at 17,
425.70 on Friday, at a turnover of 12.162 billion HK dollars (1.
559 billion U.S. dollars), against Thursday's 11.931 billion HK
dollars (1.529 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
All the four sub-indexes of the HSI registered gains, with
Finance, Utilities, Properties and Commerce &AMP; Industry rising by 1.
68 percent, 0.15 percent, 2.42 percent and 0.11 percent,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng China Enterprises Index went up 1.15 percent and Hang
Seng China-Affiliated Corp Index 0.92 percent .
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng IT Index and Hang Seng IT Portfolio Index lost 0.40
percent and 0.39 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng index dropped to below the 17,000 to close at 16,
840.98 on Monday. The index regained some momentum in the
following trading days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
