<HEADLINE> China Southern Airlines Takes over Provincial Aviation Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 4 (Xinhua) -- China Southern Airlines, one of
China's major civil aviation companies, today took over a
provincial aviation company.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that a national pillar aviation company
took over a local aviation company since the General
Administration of Civil Aviation of China, also known as CAAC,
announced that China would form three big airline groups-- Air
China, China Eastern Airlines and China Southern Airlines.
</P>
<P>
The local aviation company, Zhongyuan Airlines, was founded by
central China's Henan Province in 1986. The total asset of the
local company was 1.46 billion yuan. The company has five Boeing
737s and two home-made aircraft in operation. It offers more than
100 flights each week. It has had no air crashes in the past 14
years.
</P>
<P>
China Southern Airlines is one of the biggest airlines in China.
It provides over 2,600 flights each week and has flown more
passengers among all other civil aviation companies across the
county in the past twenty one years.
</P>
<P>
The merger will make China Southern Airlines more competitive
and be conducive to an orderly development of civil aviation in
central China.
</P>
<P>
The three new groups will include ten airlines run by the CAAC,
including Air China, China Eastern Airlines, China Southern
Airlines, China Northern Airlines and Yunnan Airlines.
</P>
<P>
In addition to these ten companies, China has 24 local airlines.
</P>
<P>
The three groups expect to have assets worth more than 40
billion yuan each, and almost equal market shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
