<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Advertisement Turnover Up 12.3 Percent in First Half Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- China's advertisement turnover
hit 28.2 billion yuan (3.9 billion US dollars) in the first half
of the year, up 12.3 percent from the corresponding period last
year.
</P>
<P>
A lion's share of the sales volume came from professional
advertisement companies, which registered 12.3 billion yuan in
sales or an annual growth rate of 24.6 percent, according to the
State Administration for Industry and Commerce today.
</P>
<P>
Food, household appliances, medicine, cosmetics, and real
estate sectors saw a hefty increase in advertising investment in
the January-June period.
</P>
<P>
The proportion of State-owned, collectively-owned, associated
firms and foreign-funded enterprises dropped while private
companies increased by 38 percent.
</P>
<P>
Profit earned through periodicals, newspapers and radios rose
by 49 percent, 20.6 percent and 24.8 percent, respectively, while
TV ads reported a negative growth of 10.5 percent for the first
time in years.
</P>
<P>
Beijing, Shanghai and Guangdong led all other cities in profit-
earnings, accounting for nearly 50 percent of the total
advertisement profits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
