<HEADLINE> Romanian National Soccer Championship Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The 2000-2001 edition of the
Romanian first soccer division begins on Friday under a new format
and with at least three teams aspiring to the national title.
</P>
<P>
There are 16 teams (comparing with 18 last season) in the first
division and the relegation system has also been changed.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the season, the teams ranking 15th and 16th will
be automatically relegated to the second division and the 13th and
14th ranked will be given the chance of a play-off with the second
ranked of the two B divisions on condition they have at least 30
points.
</P>
<P>
The main favorites for the title are Steaua, Rapid and Dinamo,
all from Bucharest. Steaua has made several good acquisitions and
the results of the training matches are encouraging.
</P>
<P>
Rapid benefits from the experience of the best Romanian coach
over the last period - Anghel Iordanescu - and has a well-balanced
team.
</P>
<P>
Dinamo, who holds the title, has certain difficulties after the
transfer period and started on the wrong foot in the international
competition season - they were prematurely eliminated by Polonia
Warsaw in Champions League.
</P>
<P>
In the inaugural match, Universitatea Craiova will play against
FC Brasov. The program of the first round to end on Monday
includes a first derby: FC National vs. Dinamo Bucharest. 
