<DOCNO> XIE20000804.0121 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Moving Eastward, Scientists Find </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 4 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-U.S. joint survey
indicates that each year Shanghai moves 8 mm eastward and Urumqi,
capital of northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region,
shifts 14 mm northeastward.
</P>
<P>
This results from the northward movement of the Indian
subcontinent, which has also caused the uplift of the Qinghai-
Tibet Plateau, according to the survey.
</P>
<P>
The survey was conducted in Shanghai, Urumqi, Alaska, Hawaii,
Japan's Kashima and Australia's Tasmania by Shanghai Observatory
and the U.S. National Aeronautics and Space Administration.
</P>
<P>
"The findings conform to the earlier theory of crustal plate
movements," said Wang Guangli, a researcher with Shanghai
Observatory, who participated in the survey.
</P>
<P>
The new findings provide a major scientific basis for further
study of the movement of the Eurasian plate, Wang added.
</P>
<P>
The survey is part of a massive research program on geodynamics
in the Asia-Pacific region launched in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The international program with the participation of a dozen
countries is designed to monitor crustal movement in the Asia-
Pacific region and probe into the laws of such natural disasters
as earthquakes and volcanic eruptions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000804.0122 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Another Suspect Responsible for June 30 Explosion Detained </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Local police in Jiangmen City
in south China's Guangdong Province today detained Liang Zhijian,
another suspect held responsible for a major explosion in a local
fireworks factory which took place on June 30.
</P>
<P>
Six other suspects have also been detained by police.
</P>
<P>
Investigators found that in March 1993, the 47 year old Liang
was an employee with the Pengjiang Branch of the Jiangmen Bureau
of Public Security. He was in charge of explosives, but abused his
power and approved Jiangmen Local Product High-Grade Fireworks
Factory to add four more workshops. This clearly violated safety
regulations.
</P>
<P>
The investigators concluded that Liang was directly
responsibility for the June 30 explosion.
</P>
<P>
According to earlier reports, at least 35 people were killed,
and 167 others were injured during the explosion. The State
Council sent a special team to investigate the cause of the
explosion.
</P>
<P>
After the explosion, Guangdong Provincial Government convened
an emergency meeting to cease the production of all fireworks
factories and manufacturers of cigarette lighters in the province.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
