<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Shanghai A Share </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Composite Index
closed at 2,026.36 points Friday, up 13.57 points or 0.67 percent
from last week's 2,012 points.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover this week stood at 64.59 billion yuan, 5.52
percent less than last week's 61.21 billion yuan, according to
Homeway, a leading online financial and securities advisory
company.
</P>
<P>
During the week, the Shanghai Composite Index created new highs
almost everyday and touched 2,041.28 points Friday. However, the
slow bullish trend indicates that the turnover was not greatly
expanded.
</P>
<P>
High-tech and Internet companies became bellwethers again this
week, boosted by the news about Tsinghua Tongfang. The company
might create 100 millionaires, each with a wealth of 10 million
yuan, and the company's price will jump up to 150 yuan per share,
according to Lu Zhicheng, the company's president.
</P>
<P>
Steel companies, ST shares and mutual funds also performed
actively. But investors were still concerned about the market
which is on the historic high level.
</P>
<P>
Another feature was that the IPO market expanded slowly. Only
four new shares debuted on the Shanghai and Shenzhen bourses and
two new A-share companies issued new shares on the Shanghai bourse.
All IPOs rose a little on the first listing day.
</P>
<P>
Fueled by sound economic development and favorable government
policies towards the stock market, the Shenzhen Composite Index
and sub-index continued to climb to new highs since they hit 600
points and 4,900 points respectively last month. The indices are
likely to stay at the high level for some time. 
