<HEADLINE> China's Fund Market on Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- China's fund market continued to
correct strongly Friday, according to Homeway, a leading online
financial and securities information provider.
</P>
<P>
Fund Jinding made its debut on the market today. It rose to its
ceiling at the beginning of the market. Surprisingly, the fund
holders were very much reluctant to participate in the trading,
with the daily turnover reaching only 576,000 fund units. The
turnover rate was only 0.25 percent for the first trading day,
implying that the fund is likely to rise in short term.
</P>
<P>
Among the 32 funds on the Shanghai and Shenzhen stock markets,
eight rose, 12 remained unchanged, and 12 declined. All the
discounted funds continued to correct strongly, digesting profits.
</P>
<P>
Restructured funds diverged. Fund Yuhua and Fund Yuze jumped,
becoming top gainers today. Fund Tongzhi dropped to its floor at
the close.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that a technical cooperation agreement was
signed between the Shanghai-based Hua'an Fund Management Co., one
of the earliest and most successful fund manager in China, and the
world industry giant, British-based Fleming Investment Management
Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is billed as the first all-round technical
cooperation marriage between Chinese fund management firms and
their foreign counterparts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
