<HEADLINE> France to Compensate Holders of Old Russian Debt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The French government will
compensate the holders of old Russian debts, most of which came
down from Russian state bonds for investing in building railways
before 1917, said the French government on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made after Russia recently paid France 400
million U.S. dollars for compensating the holders of the pre-
revolution Russian state bonds as well as French individuals and
companies whose properties were seized during the 1917 Revolution
and World War II.
</P>
<P>
The French Ministry of Economy said that a government decree on
compensating the holders of Russian debts will be issued in the
coming days and the payment will be made by the end of the year.
</P>
