<HEADLINE> Shanghai B-share Market up Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai B-share market index
edged up 0.18 points, or 0.29 percent, to close at 64.30 Friday.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover was 30.48 million U.S. dollars, compared with 28.
32 million U.S. dollars Thursday, according to Homeway, China's
leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The market advance was somehow curbed as profit-takers cropped
up in late morning session, but it managed to resume in the
afternoon on strong conviction of the near-term direction,
boosting the confidence of investors.
</P>
