<HEADLINE> URGENT: China Opposes Attempt to Get Taiwan into UN: Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- China firmly opposes any attempt
to get Taiwan into the United Nations, Chinese Foreign Ministry
Spokesman Zhu Bangzao said here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remarks in response to a move by Senegal and a few
other countries, which on August 3 (New York time) wrote to the UN
secretary-general asking for the 55th General Assembly of the UN
to consider Taiwan's "participation" in the UN. Those countries
also tried to get the Taiwan issue into the framework of UN peace
and security mechanism.
</P>
<P>
"They are attempting to create 'two Chinas' or 'one China, one
Taiwan' in the UN," Zhu said. "The move constitutes a flagrant
violation of the purposes and principles of the UN Charter, a
distortion of the nature of UN, and a gross interference in China'
s internal affairs. We are strongly indignant at and firmly oppose
such a move."  
</P>
