<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 8 People Killed by Floods in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 4 (Xinhua) -- At least eight people have been
killed by floods and landslides triggered by torrential rains in
various parts of Nepal in the last two days, a report said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Floods and landslides have also damaged roads, bridges, houses
and other infrastructure, inundated vast swathes of cultivated and
inhabited lands and killed hundreds of livestock, causing property
losses worth at least 200,000 U.S. dollars, said The Kathmandu
Post, an English daily.
</P>
<P>
About 10,000 people are left homeless after their houses and
land were inundated and damaged, the daily said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, transportation movements have been disrupted on
several highways across the country, including Prithvu and Araniko
highways, two major roads linking the capital city with the rest
of the country and China's Tibetan Autonomous Region respectively,
it said.
</P>
<P>
Floods and landslides cause heavy losses of lives and property
in Nepal during the monsoon season, which lasts from mid-June to
September every year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
