<HEADLINE> MILF Denies Involvement in Lanao Massacre </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This was the reaction of Eid Kabalu, MILF spokesman, on the
findings of the Commission on Human Rights pinpointing
responsibility of the gory crime to the MILF.
</P>
<P>
Kabalu said that based on their investigation, it was the
former guards of the Dimaporo family that perpetrated the ghastly
murder.
</P>
<P>
He identified the suspects as Coco, Ibrahim and Pamisaran, all
surnamed Cadayon, former security guards of Maranaw Plantation Inc.
</P>
<P>
