<HEADLINE> Share Prices Further Weaken in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices further weakened in
Tokyo Friday in the absence of significant positive factors, with
two major indexes hitting closing lows for this year.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 147.08 points, or 0.93
percent from Thursday's close to end at 15,667.36.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, dropped 9.59 points or 0.66 percent to 1,450.
88.
</P>
<P>
The two indexes both hit this year's closing lows.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section increased to 603.24 million
shares from Thursday's 527.30 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Toshiba was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Continued selling by foreign investors, the main driving force
in the Tokyo market, led domestic investors to sell stocks,
traders said.
</P>
<P>
Share prices were lower in 20 of the exchange's 33 business
sectors, including information technology, nonferrous metals, real
estate and wholesaling.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the banks, warehousing, rubber and mining sectors
made sharp gains.
</P>
<P>
In the issues listed on the First Section, gainers outpaced
losers 801 to 479 despite the falls in the Nikkei and TOPIX, with
113 issues closing unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
