<HEADLINE> One Killed, One Injured by House Blast in Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 4 (Xinhua) -- One girl was killed and another
wounded in a house explosion near Russia's second largest city of
St. Petersburg on Thursday night, Russian news agencies reported
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The blast went off in the stairway of an apartment house in the
settlement of Novoye Devyatkino, a suburb of St. Petersburg, at 9:
50 p.m. Moscow time (1750 GMT) Thursday, killing a 12-year-old
girl and injuring a nine-year-old girl, who were leaving the house,
the Interfax news agency cited the Russian Northwestern regional
rescue center as saying.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that the explosion was caused by a kilogram of
smoke powder that someone had left at the entrance of the stairway,
said the center.
</P>
<P>
The blast broke windows in the first and second floors of the
house and damaged a car parked nearby.
</P>
<P>
A team of police and investigators are working at the explosion
site, said the report. 
</P>
