<HEADLINE> Chinese T-Bond Trading Narrow Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- China's T-bond market extended
the mixed outlook today. Of the six current bonds, the three
listed after 1999 advanced, while the three old products declined.
</P>
<P>
Trade on treasuries stayed narrow though both the A share
composite indices on the two domestic stock exchanges ended
slightly lower today. Transaction value contracted by 813 million
yuan to 1.52 billion yuan, according to Homeway, a leading online
financial information provider.
</P>
<P>
The 10-year floating-rate 010004 jumped 0.28 percent to create
another record high of 103.49 yuan, rewriting the record high of
103.25 Wednesday. Its yield went down 0.03 percent to 2.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Bond 009905 (3.28 percent, due 2007) picked up 0.09 percent to
102.71 yuan, while bond 000696 (11.83 percent, due 2006) slid 0.09
percent to 143.42 yuan. Yields on the two bonds closed at 3.35
percent and 3.75 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The combined turnover of three-day, seven-day, 14-day and 28-
day repo transactions shrank by 3.03 billion yuan to 4.75 billion
yuan. Meanwhile, the close price of the three-day transaction
plummeted by 2.3 percentage points to 0.90 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
