<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading Turkish newspapers on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Daily News:
</P>
<P>
-- The Turkish Foreign Ministry said on Thursday both sides in
Cyprus should "mutually recognize each other's political equality
and sovereignty" in order to create a common ground for negotiation
on the island.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement, the ministry said the purpose of the
proximity talks on Cyprus in Geneva is to "prepare necessary ground
for face-to-face talks. Only after this ground is created,
negotiations could be initiated."
</P>
<P>
