1974 when Turkey sent its troops to the north following an
attempted pro-Athens coup.
</P>
<P>
Yenibinyil:
</P>
<P>
-- A report prepared by the Italian police said the outlawed
Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK) is raising fund from drug-trafficking
and organization of illegal immigration.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the PKK, which has waged a 15-year
armed struggle for self-rule in southeast Turkey, is transferring
illegal immigrants from northern Iraq via Turkey to Greece, Italy
and Germany.
</P>
<P>
Hurriyet:
</P>
<P>
-- Devlet Bahceli, leader of Turkey's ruling partner Nationalist
Action Party (MHP), is launching a new campaign to improve his
party image by forming women and youth branches within the party.
</P>
<P>
Last week, an armed clash took place at one of the party's
grassroots congress due to some youth members' radical actions. One
party member was killed in the clash.
</P>
<P>
Milliyet:
</P>
<P>
-- One Turkish official said that if Palestinian President
Yasser Arafat declares an independent state on September 13, Turkey
will not have to face a hard dilemma whether to recognize it or not
because Turkey has already recognized Palestine and has diplomatic
relations with it.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian administration has an embassy in Ankara while
Turkey has a consulate accredited to the Palestinian administration
in East Jerusalem. 
</P>
