<HEADLINE> Farmers' Telephone Installation On Fast Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Home telephone installation has
become a hot consumption spot in rural Zhejiang, one of China's
leading economic developed provinces in east coastal region.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhejiang Telcom Company's Statistics, over 800,000
lines were fixed in the countryside in the first six months of
this year, almost doubling the figure in the urban areas in the
same period.
</P>
<P>
To promote information exchange of the rural areas with outside
world and push their economic development, Zhejiang has over
recent years stressed telecommunications networks construction in
the countryside.
</P>
<P>
Through strengthening telecommunications infrastructure, the
province has realized the goal that optical cables stretched to
all the townships in 1997 and every village could have access to
telephones in 1998.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the higher growth rate of telephone installation
in rural areas than in cities, the telephone-possessing rate for
rural families is drawing close to that in cities. 
