<HEADLINE> Philippines' Inflation Rises to 4.2 Percent in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Philippines' year-on-year
inflation rose to 4.2 percent in July against 3.9 percent in June,
driven by higher inflation in food and services, the government
said Friday
</P>
<P>
The latest inflation figure brought the January-July average to
3.6 percent, still well below the government's 5-6 percent goal
this year,the National Statistics Office (NS)) said in a press
release issued here.
</P>
<P>
It was the second time this year that inflation stood at 4.2
percent after the statistics agency revised the May inflation
figure to 4.2 percent, the highest level so far this year, from
the earlier reported 4.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Year-on-year inflation in July last year stood at 5.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
"Food, beverages and tobacco and services contributed mainly to
the increase in the year-on-year inflation rate," the government
agency said.
</P>
<P>
Month-on-month inflation, however, decelerated slightly to 0.5
percent in July from 0.7 percent in June, the NSO said. 
</P>
