<HEADLINE> Tibet to Hold First Folk Arts Lantern Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Folk Arts Lantern Festival is
to be staged from August 6 through October 18 in Lhasa, Tibet, and
it is the first time the city holds such an activity.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the Lhasa city government and full of Tibetan
flavor, the festival is to display 25 groups of lanterns,
featuring national unity, dragons and other themes, according to
the organization committee of the festival.
</P>
