<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China News Digest: West on the Move (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This capital city of Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, one of the
driest areas in China, raised prices of water on August 1 to ease
water shortages.
</P>
<P>
The city raised the price of water for public utilities and
daily consumption of residents from 0.65 yuan per ton to 0.85 yuan
per ton. It also raised the price of water for government and non-
government organizations from 0.75 yuan per ton to 1.00 yuan per
ton.
</P>
<P>
Water prices for industrial enterprises went up from 0.85 yuan
per ton to 1.10 yuan per ton. Water prices in the service industry
rose from 0.95 yuan per ton to 1.20 yuan per ton.
</P>
<P>
The city also raised water prices for some specific trades to 2.
50 yuan per ton. These trades include saunas, entertainment halls,
luxury hotels, pure water manufacturers, dance and karaoke halls,
bars and feet massage clinics.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing Allowed to Issue Visas
</P>
<P>
Chongqing in southwest China has became the first city in west
China that is authorized to issue visas to overseas travelers.
</P>
<P>
From August 1, overseas visitors flying into the city can
obtain visas directly from local visa department of public
security bureau at the Jiangbei International Airport in the city.
They will no longer have to travel to other cities for a visa.
</P>
<P>
Most of the 20 cities that are authorized to issue visas for
overseas visitors are located in eastern and coastal areas of
China.
</P>
<P>
The move authorize Chongqing to issue visas aims at attracting
more overseas visitors to the city and facilitate the Chinese
government's drive to develop China's western regions.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing has connecting flights with Japan, Thailand, Germany,
Korea and many other foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing Industries Turns From Deficits to Profits
</P>
<P>
The industrial sector of Chongqing, the largest metropolis in
western China, has turned its four-year deficits into profits in
the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The state-owned enterprises and non-state firms with annual
sales income of five million yuan in Chongqing made 39 million
yuan in profits in the first six months, against losses of 629
million yuan in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The industrial output value of state-owned enterprises came to
31 billion yuan, up 10.2 percent while joint stock firms rose 29
percent at 1.2 billion yuan. The output of enterprises with funds
from abroad was 5.8 billion yuan, a 21 percent increase.
</P>
<P>
Production sales rose to 96 percent. The value of goods for
export was 2.1 billion yuan by the end of June, up by 75 percent
compared with the figure a year ago. The output value of new
products came to 8.5 billion yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
