<HEADLINE> China's Most Powerful Inner-Combustion Locomotives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, August 4 (Xinhua) -- China's two most powerful inner-
combustion locomotives have been manufactured by the Dalian
Locomotives and Trains Factory in northeast China's port city of
Dalian.
</P>
<P>
The two engines, each with a power of 3,820 kW, are for
passenger and cargo transport. The driving facilities are jointly
developed by the factory and a U.S. research institute.
</P>
<P>
The highest speed of the locomotive for drawing passenger
trains can reach 180 km per hour, while the engine for cargo
transport can pull a maximum load of 5,000 tons. 
