<DOCNO> XIE20000804.0246 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albania's Foreign Debts Soar to New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Albania's total foreign debts
accumulated since 1992 have soared to a high of 588 million U.S.
dollars, about one quarter of the country's annual Gross Domestic
Product, the local Our Times daily newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
The largest creditor to Albania is the International
Development Association,to which Albania owes 292 million U.S.
dollars, followed in turn by Italy, Germany, France and Japan,
according to the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
As Albania's economy has not yet recovered, the country is
ranks among the poorest and most heavily indebted nations, it said.
</P>
<P>
Over recent years, the Albanian government has frequently asked
its creditors to reschedule the repayment of debts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
