<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Panama to Build Second Canal Bridge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The Panamanian government has
instructed a high-level committee to help facilitate the
construction of the second bridge on the Panama Canal.
</P>
<P>
This was announced on Thursday by Economy and Finance Minister
Victor N. Juliao Gelonch, who said that the bidding for the
construction will take place very soon.
</P>
<P>
He said this project, which will cost 110 million U.S. dollars,
is expected to be completed on March 2004.
</P>
<P>
The Public Works Ministry will be in charge of the execution of
the project, to be financed by the central government at the first
stage and by the Panama Canal Authority afterwards.
</P>
<P>
The six-lane bridge will be located north of the Pedro Miguel
floodgate and open to the public free of charge.
</P>
<P>
The old bridge built in 1968 will be restored and kept in
service, so as to control the increasingly busy traffic every day,
officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
