<DOCNO> XIE20000804.0248 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico Makes Efforts to Control Tobacco Abuse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican government is making
great efforts to control the abuse of tobacco, said a National
Commissioner for Control of Addictions, Ernesto Enriquez Rubio, on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that nearly 122 people in Mexico die from the
abuse of tobacco every day. About 27 percent of the smoking
population are between 12 and 65 years old, while 10 percent are
adolescents, said Enriquez on the occasion of launching the
Program Against Tobacco Use.
</P>
<P>
Aiming to solve the tobacco-abusing problem, the government has
worked out the Program Against Tobacco Use to reinforce inter-
institutional control mechanisms by using legislative and
preventive measures, said Enriquez.
</P>
<P>
He went on to explain that the program has an evaluation scheme
that may provide measures necessary to control tobacco abuse in
the short as well as in the long run, with the help of trustworthy
indicators.
</P>
<P>
In the anti-tobacco campaign, 47 organizations and institutions
in the sectors of health, education, legislature, youth,
environmental protection and communications will participate, said
Enriquez.
</P>
<P>
He cited the findings by the World Health Organization (WHO) as
saying that smoking is a direct and indirect cause of more than 3.
5 million diseases every year around the world, with a third of
them occurring in developing countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
