<HEADLINE> Casiraghi May Sue Chelsea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Italian striker Pierluigi
Casiraghi, who has been out of action for 20 months with a serious
knee injury, may sue English Premier League Chelsea for the club
is going to end his contract two years early.
</P>
<P>
Casiraghi, who injured his knee in a match against West Ham in
November, 1998, had played only 10 games for the team, and was
reported to have received 10 operations on his knee.
</P>
<P>
Chelsea has paid 32-year-old Casiraghi 25,000 pounds ($37,500)
per week during his rest but informed the former Lazio player that
he had six months to prove his fitness. The six months is due in
two weeks.
</P>
<P>
But Chelsea has already obtained a 4 million pound ($6 million)
insurance payout and Casiraghi, who refuses to believe his career
is over, is claiming he deserves his future wages as compensation.
</P>
<P>
His agents have contacted lawyers on making an appeal to the
Premier League's board or taking possible civil action in the
courts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
