<DOCNO> XIE20000804.0255 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 300,000 Economic Offenses Handled in Half Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Local administrations for
industry and commerce handled some 319,000 economic offenses and
irregularities in the first half of this year, up 20 percent from
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The total value of these cases stood at 4.89 billion yuan (672
million U.S. dollars), the State Administration for Industry and
Commerce said this week.
</P>
<P>
Some 46 percent of the irregularities involved unfair
competition, such as counterfeiting of trade marks. The value of
such offenses almost doubled the figure of the corresponding
period last year.
</P>
<P>
During the six-month period, local administrations also cracked
down on 1,879 smuggling cases, with goods implicated valued at 640
million yuan (88.7 million U.S. dollars), a slight drop from the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The number of reported economic offenses in share-holding
companies and foreign-funded enterprises declined while that of
those associated companies shot up by a big margin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
