<HEADLINE> Grant Hill Traded to Orlando Magic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The Detroit Pistons completed
a sign-and-trade deal with Orlando Magic on Thursday, sending star
free agent Grant Hill to Orlando in exchange for Chucky Atkins and
Ben Wallace.
</P>
<P>
The deal was a blessing to all parties concerned as five-time
All-Star Hill pledged earlier that he would sign with the Magic
while Wallace and Atkins said they wanted to go to Detroit.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the deal also allows Detroit to stay under the salary
cap, said Pistons president of the basketball operations Joe
Dumars.
</P>
<P>
Atkins, undrafted in 1996 and played two seasons in Croatia,
averaged 9.5 points on .424 shooting with 3.7 assists in 19.8
minutes off the bench for Orlando last year.
</P>
<P>
Wallace, also undrafted in 1996 and played three seasons with
Washington Wizards, averaged 4.8 points on .503 shooting with 8.2
rebounds and 1.6 blocks in 24.2 minutes per game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
