<HEADLINE> China, US to Construct Tourism Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, August 4 (Xinhua) -- China and the United States
will jointly construct a big tourism zone in north China,
including restoring some imperial buildings.
</P>
<P>
The tourism zone, to be built in Chengde city of Hebei province,
three hours' drive from Beijing. will be on the venue of a famous
summer resort for emperors and royal members of the Qing Dynasty (
17th-20th century).
</P>
<P>
The zone will cover an area of 57 square kilometers and involve
an investment of 3.6 billion yuan (some 400 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
At least two U.S. companies and a Hong Kong company will take
part in the program to construct the imperial gardens and palaces
and some recreational facilities.
</P>
<P>
Millions of people visit Chengde every year to see historical
sites, but many of them complained that there is few entertaining
activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
