<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 7,000-Year-Old Site Discovered in Three Gorges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese archeologists have
discovered a site dating back to 7,000 years ago in the Three
Gorges on the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
They said that this is the first time a Neolithic site at its
early stage was found in Chongqing Municipality and Sichuan
Province on the upper reaches of the Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
A large number of stone, bone and pottery tools and vessels
have been unearthed in Fengdu City, inscribed with simple patterns.
</P>
<P>
The relics are believed to have relations with prehistoric
cultures in the middle reaches of the Yangtze. The finding
overthrew the conclusion that cultures in the upper and lower
reaches of the Yangtze were isolated.
</P>
<P>
The archeologists guess that the Three Gorges once served as a
cultural link between tribes in different regions in ancient times.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000804.0267 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Color Diamond Discovered in Southern Shaanxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese geologists have found a
rare mineral species -- black granite -- at Jiangkou Town,
Ningshan County of northwest China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Three professors from the China Geological University confirmed
that it is the first time that the rare stone, also known as black
gold color diamond, has ever been discovered in China.
</P>
<P>
Proved reserves of the color diamond stands at one million cu m.
</P>
<P>
The major components of the black gold color diamond include 50
percent of hornblende, 23 percent of hypersthene, 12 percent of
plagioclase, and certain proportions of olivine, biotite and
ironstone, according to experts.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that the quality and radioactivity index of the
stone are all up to the state-set standards, and the stone is a
kind of high-class decorative material.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
