<HEADLINE> 2 Billion Yuan for Information Industry Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, August 4 (Xinhua) -- China's prestigious Haixin Group
has recently broken earth here to build its Information Industry
Park, pouring a huge investment of 2 billion yuan (240 million U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Located in Qingdao in eastern coastal Shandong Province, the
high-tech park, covering an area of 80 hectares, will be a base of
electronic and telecommunications produce and information services,
local official sources said.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the park marks a switch of Haixin from a
traditional household appliance producer to an information service
and products provider, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The park will mainly turn out Internet-related information
products, such as multimedia TV set, hi-resolution TV set, new
generation of CDMA mobile phones, computer, Linux firewall and
interconnected cashier.
</P>
<P>
When the project is completed and goes into operation, it will
bring Haixin an annual sales income of 25 billion yuan (3 billion
U.S. dollars).  
</P>
