<HEADLINE> Science, Technology Help Western China's Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Science and technology will help
western China to boost its agricultural development and improve
the environment, China Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
Science and technology administrations there will be encouraged
to work out state-of-the-art development plans with help from the
Ministry of Science and Technology.
</P>
<P>
About 20 million yuan, invested by the ministry, plus cash from
regional governments, will be used to fuel the campaign, said Liu
Yanhua, director of the ministry's Department for Rural and Social
Development.
</P>
<P>
New techniques of anti-desertification, afforestation and
growing high-yield cash crops, which will help improve the living
standards of farmers there, will be funded with the money.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will implement the "Spark Plan", which has yielded
remarkable results in eastern rural areas since it was launched in
1986, in the western regions to boost agricultural production
through advanced technology, Liu said.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, officials from western China will receive
administration skills training to better manage the long-term
development in western regions, according to sources from the
Rural Development Center of the ministry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
