<HEADLINE> Qinghua University to Have More CPC members among Young Teachers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- About 140 young teachers in China
's prestigious Qinghua University have recently applied for the
membership of the Communist Party of China (CPC), as part of the
university's efforts to cultivate excellent youth.
</P>
<P>
According to Thursday's "Guangming Daily", over 100 young
teachers joined the CPC between 1994 and 1998.
</P>
<P>
The university sources noted that young teachers not only take
the responsibility of training successors of the socialist system,
but they are the successors themselves, and will greatly influence
the development and future of Qinghua.
</P>
<P>
Qinghua University have tried hard to created favorable
environment for young teachers including appointing 201 young
teachers to professors and raising special housing fund for young
teachers.
</P>
<P>
An official with the university disclosed that 74.6 percent of
the 122 Qinghua professors under the age of 45 are CPC members.
