<HEADLINE> Bio-medicine Base Primarily Shaped in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai has primarily shaped the
bio-medicine base which is full of high-tech pharmaceutical
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
All the enterprises in the Zhangjiang High-tech Industrial Park,
in the Pudong New District, reached productive value worth of 2.4
billion yuan (290 million U.S. dollars) in 1999, with a 50 percent
rise compared with that in 1998, Wenhui Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
A total of 18 pharmaceutical internationals, such as Roche,
Smith-Kline Beecham (SB) Pharmaceutical Corporation, 999
Enterprise Group and others, have invested more than 2.5 billion
yuan into their affiliated plants in the industrial park.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai municipal government will pour another 445 million
yuan into the park, which has been proposed as a "medicine valley"
in China, the Shanghai-based newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
A high-tech incubator, with an area of 50,000 square meters,
provides many preferential terms to 30 innovative enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The park also includes many key academic organizations,
including Shanghai Medicine Institute of the Chinese Academy of
Sciences (CAS), the Chinese National Human Genome Center (CHGC) at
Shanghai, the national new medicine selection center, the national
new medicine safety appraisal center, Shanghai medicine research
and development center, Shanghai medicine innovation center, and
the traditional Chinese medicine engineering research institute in
Shanghai, the newspaper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
