<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Floral Festival Attracts 16 Countries And Regions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Some 300 companies from 16
countries and regions will participate in an international floral
festival to be held in this capital of southwest China's Yunnan
province.
</P>
<P>
The festival will be jointly held by the government of the
province, called a "garden of nature", and the China Flower
Association from September 28 to October 3.
</P>
<P>
The event will be a grand international horticultural gala
following the '99 Kunming Horticulture Expo, government sources
said.
</P>
<P>
The attendants will come from Israel, the Netherlands, and
South American countries as well as China's Hong Kong and Macao,
according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to good geological conditions and subtropical climate,
Yunnan boasts a variety of about 2,500 wild flowers.
</P>
<P>
The province's flower industry has been developing much rapidly
in recent years, with flower growing area expanding to 1,729 ha in
1999 from 16 ha in 1994. And the province's flower sale now
occupies 40 percent of the domestic market.
</P>
<P>
During the floral festival, various activities will be held to
entertain citizens and visitors, including an opening ceremony,
festooned vehicle parade, flower exhibitions, flower setting shows,
flower photographing shows, and technological seminars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
