<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Business as Brisk as Usual in Shanghai Bars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Business is as brisk as usual in
Shanghai bars this summer, despite more people prefer stay home
all night surfing on the net.
</P>
<P>
Neon lit up every Shanghai bar street -- Hengshan Road,
Xiangyang Road, Yandong Road and Shaoxin Road, all jammed with
youngsters whose hair styles are as fashionable as their dresses.
</P>
<P>
"It is a place just for relaxation and relieving feelings, why
not come here?" said a university teacher, who was reluctant to
give his name.
</P>
<P>
Bars in Shanghai sprang out over night several years ago. They
were first venues for foreigners and white-collar Chinese working
in foreign-invested companies, but now they entertain all kinds of
people.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai bars have always been cool, offering not only beverage
and rock'n'roll but also other things.
</P>
<P>
For example, there is a cloth bar on Guangyuan road, which
provides antique sewing machines for funs of dress making. "It is
trendy for young people to weave something with their own hands,"
said a client.
</P>
<P>
Yanghua, a clerk of the bar, said that most of her clients are
weaving the colorful cloth as gifts for their boy friends.
</P>
<P>
"Swordplay Bar", decorated with huge pictures of Zorro, a
French Robinhood, and princess Harmlet, has something special -- a
place for hero admirers.
</P>
<P>
People come here for due, and the bar provides them with a
platform and fleurets. The fights always end in happiness in
accordance with the spirits of the Olympic games.
</P>
<P>
"We had thought that the place was boys' favorite, but to my
astonishment, more girls prefer it," said the bar's boss.
</P>
<P>
Although some bars were reported to have been involved in drug
abuse and prostitution, and a vice crackdown is being carried out,
Shanghai authorities say most of the bars are providing legal
service.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
