<DOCNO> XIE20000804.0285 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinjiang Drafts Plan To Develop The Region (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, August 3 (Xinhua) -- According to the Xinjiang
Development Plan under the national strategy to develop China's
western regions, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region will invest 900 billion yuan in fixed assets in the next
decade.
</P>
<P>
By 2005, the region will invest a total of 100 billion yuan in
more than 70 key projects, including infrastructure construction,
environmental protection and development of pillar industries.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, Xinjiang will become the top production
base of cotton, cotton cloth and cotton yarn in China. It will
also strive to become one of the largest production bases of grain,
animal produce, fruit and sugar. It also plans to become the
largest oil, natural gas and petrochemical base in western China.
</P>
<P>
To achieve these goals, the region plans to secure an annual
economic growth of over 10 percent in the next few years.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
