<HEADLINE> 3.8 Million People Infected with HIV/AIDS in Sub-Saharan Africa in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- About 3.8 million or 68 percent of
the total 5.6 million people throughout the world who were
infected with HIV/AIDS in 1999 live in Sub-Saharan Africa,
according to a report of World Health Organization (WHO) available
here Friday.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year 23.3 million people in Sub-Saharan
Africa were estimated to be living with HIV/AIDS, accounting for
64 percent of 33.6 million in the world.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1999 a total of 16.3 million people across the
world died of HIV/AIDS, of which 13.7 million or 84 percent were
in Sub-Saharan Africa, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
