<HEADLINE> French Firm To Invest in Venezuelan Aluminum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Venezuelan de Guayana
Corporation (CVG) has chosen French Pechiney Company as it new
partner, which will make important investments in the Venezuelan
aluminum industry with its affiliate Bauxilum.
</P>
<P>
The French firm will spend 260 million U.S. dollars in
modifications to the Bauxilum plant to increase the outcome from 1.
6 million tons to 2.2 million tons, said CVG president Antonio
Lopez Reina, quoted Friday by the press.
</P>
<P>
It will also make new technological contributions and will
enter new and better markets for the final product. The Pechiney
firm will receive in exchange a guarantee of aluminum supply for
all its production, said Lopez Reina.
</P>
<P>
The CVG president said he is confident of the prompt completion
of the procedures required for the signing of contract to benefit
both sides. 
</P>
</TEXT>
