<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Plane Crash Kills Former U.S. State Senator, Wife </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The single-engine plane carrying Thomas Allgood Sr. and his
wife, Thelma, crashed outside Daniel Field in Augusta, where they
lived. Pilot Steve Patterson also was killed.
</P>
<P>
The plane took off shortly before 8 a.m. local time and
exploded when it hit the ground, said Beach Scott, an investigator
with the National Transportation Safety Board.
</P>
<P>
There were no reports of injuries on the ground.
</P>
<P>
Thomas Allgood, a Democrat, was elected to the Georgia Senate
in 1976 and became majority leader in 1981 and served until 1991,
when he decided to leave the Senate. He became a regent two years
later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
