<HEADLINE> London, Paris Stocks Ring Up Gains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The London and Paris stock markets
closed with an upswing Friday, as technology and
telecommunications stocks rebounded from big losses a day earlier
and concerns over U.S. interest rates eased.
</P>
<P>
Buoyant telecom stocks helped London's FTSE 100 to a solid gain.
The index closed at 6,363.5 points, up 46.4 or 0.73 percent, a
gain of 27.8 from a week ago.
</P>
<P>
Telecoms giant Vodafone surged 5.4 percent to provide 39 of the
telecom sector's 46 points on the FTSE upside. Gainers were in a
three-to-two majority as the index edged up 0.4 percent on the
week as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Cable &AMP; Wireless rose 3.2 percent and Colt Telecom gained 4.4
percent. Companies supplying the telecom industry with components
and gear also gained. Optical component maker Bookham soared 9.3
percent and chip designer ARM Holdings rose 6.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The pan-European FTSE Eurotop 300, a broader index of the
region's largest stocks, rose 1 percent. The index's information
technology sector added 3.7 percent and the telecom sub-index rose
2.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The CAC 40 index in Paris closed up 106 points, or 1.7 percent,
to 6,454.17, bounding back from Thursday's 2.7-percent decline.
Network equipment maker Alcatel rose 5.1 percent. For the week,
the blue-chip French index was up 0.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, the DAX index ended at 7,016.59 points, down 21.
32 or 0.30 percent, a loss of 111.71 over the week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
