<HEADLINE> Mexican Popocatepetl Volcano Spewing Gas, Ashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Popocatepetl volcano,
located in the center of Mexico, spewed Friday in two occasions
columns of steam and ashes up to 5,000 meters above its crater,
according to sources at the Disasters Prevention National Center (
Cenapred).
</P>
<P>
The Cenapred specialists said the colossus exhalations that
lasted two minutes in its most intense phase do not mean a danger
for the almost half a million people, who live on the volcano
slopes.
</P>
<P>
The yellow alert flag is kept up and people are asked not to
get more than seven kilometers from the crater, in prevention of a
sudden explosion, said the experts.
</P>
<P>
Civil Protection authorities warned of the possibility of a
rain of ashes in the next hours over the settlements close to the
volcano.
</P>
<P>
The Popocatepetl summit, 5,452 meters above sea level, is
located on the dividing line between the central states of Morelos,
Mexico, and Puebla, some 75 kilometers east of Mexico City.
</P>
</TEXT>
