<HEADLINE> Slovakia's Foreign Exchange Reserves Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Slovakia's foreign exchange
reserves reached 5.97 billion U.S. dollars by August 2, an
increase of 1.59 billion dollars from that at the end of last year,
the Slovak National Bank announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest statistics, the Slovak National Bank's
foreign reserves rose 516 million dollars to 3.94 billion dollars
in the same period. The foreign reserves of commercial banks
jumped by 1.08 billion dollars to 2.03 billion dollars in the
mentioned period.
</P>
<P>
Economic analysts attributed the growing foreign reserves to
strong investment flows. Deutsche Telekom, Europe's biggest
telecommunication company, paid 1 billion euro (950 million U.S.
dollars) for a 51 percent stake in Slovak Telecom last month.
