<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Rise Modestly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks ended higher
Friday as a new unemployment report lessened the threat of more
hikes in interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 61.17 at 10,767.75,
extending its gain of 19.05 points Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The technology heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 27.48 at 3,787.
36, slipping from a gain of more than 70 points earlier in the
trading. The composite rose 101.42 points in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor'
s 500 index rose 10.37 at 1,462.93.
</P>
<P>
The market rose after the U.S. Labor Department reported that
the nation's unemployment rate held steady at 4 percent in July,
near a three-decade low. The report showed a fresh sign that the
tight job market might be easing a bit and the new data relieved
fears of more interest rate hikes.
</P>
<P>
The overall jobless rate touched a 30-year low of 3.9 percent
in April before rising to 4.1 percent in May and then edging back
down to 4 percent for the past two months. The Federal Reserve has
closely watched the jobless data because the extremely tight labor
market would accelerate inflation.
</P>
<P>
A stew of the recent reports indicated that the U.S. economy is
slowing after six hikes in interest rates in the past 13 months.
But last week's report showing a stronger-than-expected economic
growth of 5.2 percent at an annual rate in the second quarter
renewed worries about more rate hikes among investors.
</P>
<P>
Investors believed the new jobless report today may prompt the
Federal Reserve to leave rates unchanged at the August 22 meeting.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 6.08 at 657.79 and the American Stock
Exchange index rose 1.39 at 907.97. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies rose 4.18 at 503.63.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 5-to-3 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,727 up, 1,124 down and 506
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 943.74 million shares from 1.04 billion
in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
