<HEADLINE> Germany's Manufacturing Orders Post Fifth Monthly Gain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
Berlin, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Germany's seasonnally-adjusted
index of manufacturing orders rose by 0.4 percent in June for the
fifth consecutive month this year, according to the Ministry of
Finance on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The continued rise is mainly attributed to foreign orders
which increased by 1.6 percent in June, while domestic orders
dipped by 0.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures have been surprising to many economists who
expected a slump after months of surge in demand for German
manufactured products.
</P>
<P>
Germany, which saw a weak increase of 1.5 percent in GDP, is
believed to double that figure in the first half of this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
