<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Electoral Council Declares Chavez President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Venezuelan National Electoral
Council (CNE) proclaimed Friday President Hugo Chavez reelected in
the July 30 elections.
</P>
<P>
Chavez, who will govern during the next six years, according to
the new constitution, thanked in his speech the CNE for the
support to the electoral process.
</P>
<P>
The president called on any agency or person who might harbor
doubts or reclamations related to the CNE results, to address
itself in a peaceful and democratic way to the corresponding
authorities.
</P>
<P>
He said that the electoral process and the behavior of
Venezuelans in the elections were successful in general.
</P>
<P>
Last Sunday, Venezuelans elected him to a fresh six-year term
and handed his political coalition a majority of state governments
and congressional seat. 
